| `test_flatten_dict_flat` | Tests a flat dictionary with no nesting. |
| `test_flatten_dict_empty_dict` | Tests an empty dictionary. |
| `test_flatten_dict_with_empty_key` | Tests a dictionary with an empty string key. |
| `test_flatten_dict_with_parent_key` | Tests the function with a custom `parent_key` argument. |
| `test_flatten_dict_with_custom_separator` | Tests the function with a custom `sep` argument. |
| `test_flatten_dict_with_nested_parent_key` | Tests a more complex nested structure with a parent key. |
| `test_flatten_dict_non_dict_input` | Ensures that passing a non-dictionary (like a list) raises a `TypeError`. |
| `test_flatten_dict_non_string_separator` | Ensures that passing a non-string `sep` raises a `TypeError`. |
| `test_flatten_dict_non_string_parent_key` | Ensures that passing a non-string `parent_key` raises a `TypeError`. |
| `test_flatten_dict_invalid_key_type` | Ensures that passing a dictionary with non-string keys raises a `TypeError`. |

